I am not sure if the second part of your information is correct. As of now, 36 seats remain (all of them are reserved seats) and all seats were reserved to begin with (for EECS/CS majors) as non-majors cannot enroll themselves in Phase 1.

In the past, 168 has not expanded unfortunately.

No priority for anyone on the waitlist regardless of major/status.

168 is a really popular class and tends to fill up quicker than any other CS class, historically.

My phase 1 is tomorrow at 12:30. I really want to take 168 this fall and I am an eecs major. Right now there are currently 39 seats left, but it also says that only 466/525 reserved seats are filled (59 remaining). If these 39 seats are filled, but there are still reserved seats remaining, would I be able to enroll? Is there any chance 168 will be expanded at all? Will my status as a declared major increase my chances of getting the class/put me higher on the waitlist if it comes to that?
